Each evening bottled water was placed next to the beds - something one never gets even at the most upscale hotels in Europe.	The staff was great and the ambiance upscale hip but not pretentious or uncomfortable in any way.	Sometimes it hard to imagine that you can find in a small hotel the same quality of service that you expect in one big five-star hotel.	The only reason I'm not giving St. Sulpice the full five stars is, while still nice, the rooms could stand for new carpet and paint and possibly new televisions.	(We are not hip or upscale!)